## PART 2: 100 LOW-COST, HIGH-IMPACT IMPROVEMENTS
*These improvements focus on performance, user experience, codebase health, and operational efficiency. Most are essentially free to implement and will streamline scaling.*

### Performance & Speed (1-20)
1. **Implement Next.js Image Component everywhere:** Ensure `next/image` is used for all images to get automatic WebP/AVIF formatting and lazy loading.
2. **Preload Critical Fonts:** Add `rel="preload"` for the primary fonts in the document head to avoid Flash of Unstyled Text (FOUT).
3. **Dynamic Import for Heavy Components:** Use `next/dynamic` to lazy-load non-critical components (like the Cart Drawer or Quick View modal) until triggered.
4. **Optimize Firestore Queries:** Add `limit()` to queries on the homepage (like Latest Drops) to avoid over-fetching data.
5. **Implement LocalStorage Caching:** Cache basic catalog items (non-inventory sensitive) in Zustand so returning users load the shop instantly.
6. **Remove Unused CSS/Tailwind Classes:** Run PurgeCSS (built into Tailwind) strictly, ensuring no dead utility classes bloat the CSS bundle.
7. **Compress All Static Brand Assets:** Run placeholder images and hero backgrounds through TinyPNG or Squoosh.
8. **Enable Gzip/Brotli Compression:** Ensure the hosting provider (e.g., Vercel) is serving compressed assets.
9. **Reduce Re-renders:** Wrap complex components in `React.memo` and use `useCallback` for functions passed down to lists (like `addToCart` on product arrays).
10. **Implement React Suspense:** Use Suspense boundaries during data fetching for smoother partial page loads.
11. **Throttle/Debounce Scroll Events:** Ensure `useScroll` from Framer Motion isn't triggering excessive DOM updates by using `useTransform` efficiently.
12. **Optimize Video Backgrounds:** If adding videos, use compressed `.mp4` or `.webm` formats, mute them, and use `playsInline`.
13. **Defer Non-Critical Scripts:** If using Google Analytics or Pixel, load them using Next.js `next/script` with `strategy="lazyOnload"`.
14. **Use Vercel Edge Functions:** Move simple API routes (like returning a promo code list) to Edge runtime for near-zero cold starts.
15. **Sprite SVG Icons:** Combine multiple SVG icons into a single sprite sheet to reduce HTTP requests, though Lucide React already handles this well.
16. **Preconnect to External Domains:** Add `<link rel="preconnect" href="https://firestore.googleapis.com">` to speed up database connection time.
17. **Pagination/Infinite Scroll in Admin:** Don't load all 100+ products at once in the admin panel; use cursor-based pagination.
18. **Avoid Heavy Libraries:** Keep using `date-fns` over `moment.js`, and avoid heavy physics libraries if CSS animations suffice.
19. **Cache API Routes:** Add `Cache-Control` headers (`s-maxage`, `stale-while-revalidate`) to public API endpoints like `/api/products`.
20. **Monitor Bundle Size:** Install `@next/bundle-analyzer` to routinely check what is bloating the build.

### User Experience (UX) & Conversion (21-40)
21. **Persistent Cart:** Standard Zustand `persist` is in place, but ensure it handles schema changes gracefully (versioning).
22. **Guest Checkout Flow:** Never force users to create an account to buy. Allow full guest checkout with optional account creation post-purchase.
23. **Toast Actionability:** Add an "Undo" or "View Cart" button directly inside the Sonner toast notification when an item is added.
24. **Smart Search Highlighting:** In the search dropdown, bold the part of the word that matches the user's typed query.
25. **Filter by Size Available:** Let users filter the shop by "My Size" so they don't click products that are out of stock for them.
26. **Hover Pre-fetching:** Add `prefetch={true}` to `<Link>` components for popular items (like in the Hero CTA) so the page loads instantly on click.
27. **Sticky "Add to Cart":** On mobile, keep the "Add to Cart" button sticky at the bottom of the screen when the user scrolls down the product description.
28. **Cross-Selling in Cart:** Show 1-2 cheap accessory recommendations (like a beanie or keychain) directly inside the Cart Drawer.
29. **Estimated Delivery Dates:** Show "Order today, estimated delivery by [Date]" near the checkout button based on a simple +5 day logic.
30. **Trust Badges:** Add subtle secure payment icons (Visa, Mastercard, Stripe) under the checkout button.
31. **Out of Stock State:** Allow users to click on out-of-stock sizes and enter an email to "Notify Me When Available."
32. **Clear Error States:** On forms (like promo codes), don't just clear the input; show a specific "Code Expired" or "Invalid Code" red text below.
33. **Exit Intent Popup:** Very sparingly, use a simple brutalist modal offering 10% off if a new user tries to leave with items in the cart.
34. **Currency Auto-Detection:** Auto-switch the ZAR/USD toggle based on the user's IP address (can use Vercel geolocation headers).
35. **Tap-to-Enlarge Gallery:** Allow mobile users to tap the product image to open a full-screen swipeable lightbox.
36. **Skeleton Loaders:** Instead of the text "LOADING...", build a CSS skeleton loader that matches the shape of the product cards for perceived speed.
37. **Scroll to Top Button:** A subtle arrow that appears on long pages (like Shop) to snap the user back to the header.
38. **Micro-copy Polish:** Change generic buttons from "Submit" to action-oriented text like "UNLOCK DROP" or "SECURE ITEM".
39. **Keyboard Accessibility:** Ensure all custom drawers and modals can be closed by pressing the `Escape` key (already mostly handled, but verify).
40. **Recently Viewed Tracker:** Store the last 4 clicked product IDs in local storage and display a "RECENTLY VIEWED" row at the bottom of products.

### Codebase Health & Developer Experience (DX) (41-60)
41. **Strict TypeScript:** Enable `"strict": true` in [tsconfig.json](file:///c:/Users/kunta/Desktop/Projects/BIZ/AWA/Swagod/base_web/SWAGOD/tsconfig.json) and fix all `any` types to prevent future runtime crashes.
42. **Component File Structure:** Move specific sub-components (like `AdminProductsTable`, `AdminProductsForm`) into their own files instead of massive 300-line pages.
43. **Environment Variable Validation:** Use a library like `zod` to validate all `process.env` variables on server startup so edge cases don't fail silently.
44. **Husky & Lint-Staged:** Set up pre-commit hooks to run Prettier and ESLint automatically before pushing code to GitHub.
45. **Centralized Constants:** Create a `lib/constants.ts` for things like `FEE_SHIPPING_THRESHOLD = 2000`, `TAX_RATE = 0.15`, preventing magic numbers in code.
46. **SEO Helmet Component:** Create a unified `SEO` wrapper component that easily injects dynamic Meta, OpenGraph, and Twitter card tags per page.
47. **Custom Hooks Extraction:** Extract logic like `useClickOutside` or `useWindowSize` into reusable `/hooks` directories.
48. **Firebase Admin vs Client Separation:** Clearly separate `lib/firebase-admin.ts` (server-only) from `lib/firebase-client.ts` to avoid exposing secrets or bundling heavy admin SDKs to the client.
49. **Error Boundaries:** Implement a React Error Boundary wrapping the main layout to catch component crashes and show a branded "SYSTEM FAILURE" fallback instead of a blank white screen.
50. **Centralized API Error Handler:** Create a utility wrapper for API routes to standardize error JSON responses (e.g., `{ success: false, error: '...' }`).
51. **Theme Variable Centralization:** Move all specialized hex codes (like primary orange) into `tailwind.config.ts` rather than hardcoding arbitrary `text-[#FF4400]` classes.
52. **Deprecation Warnings:** Comment legacy APIs or components with `@deprecated` JSDoc tags to warn future devs not to use them.
53. **Automated Dependency Updates:** Setup GitHub Dependabot to automatically open PRs for minor package updates (Next.js, Tailwind).
54. **Clean up Local Storage Keys:** Add a constant prefix to all local storage keys (e.g., `SWGD_CART`, `SWGD_THEME`) to prevent collision with other localhost apps during dev.
55. **Alias Configuration:** Ensure `@/` mapping is used exclusively, rather than confusing relative imports (`../../../components/...`).
56. **Remove `console.log`:** Use an ESLint rule to enforce removing raw `console.log` in production, utilizing a custom logger or Vercel logs instead.
57. **Standardized Naming Conventions:** Enforce PascalCase for components, camelCase for functions, and UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants.
58. **API Route Rate Limiting:** Implement basic Upstash Redis rate limiting on critical routes (like Add to Cart, Login) to prevent DDoS or spam.
59. **Database Seed Script:** Create a `seed.ts` file that can instantly wipe and repopulate a test database with mock products for fast local onboarding.
60. **Meaningful Commit Messages:** Adopt Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`) to generate automatic changelogs.

### SEO, Accessibility & Growth (61-80)
61. **Dynamic Sitemap Generation:** Use `next-sitemap` to auto-generate `sitemap.xml` and `robots.txt` based on the active product IDs in the database.
62. **JSON-LD Schema Markup:** Inject Product Schema (Price, Availability, Image) into the `<head>` of product pages so Google shows rich snippets in search results.
63. **Semantic HTML Elements:** Ensure the codebase uses `<article>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>` correctly instead of endless `<div>` tags.
64. **Aria-Labels on Icon Buttons:** All buttons that only have an icon (Cart, Hamburger) must have `aria-label="View Cart"` for screen readers.
65. **Image Alt Text Automation:** If an admin forgets to add alt text, auto-fallback to parsing the product title (e.g., `alt={product.title + " view"}`).
66. **Focus Rings:** Instead of completely hiding `outline-none`, style the `:focus-visible` state with a sharp primary color border for keyboard navigators.
67. **Skip to Main Content Link:** Add a hidden link at the very top of the DOM that becomes visible on `Tab` press, bypassing the large navigation header.
68. **Color Contrast Compliance:** Run a Lighthouse check to ensure the dark grey text on black backgrounds passes AA accessibility contrast ratios.
69. **OpenGraph Images via Edge:** Use `@vercel/og` to automatically generate unique social sharing images for every product using its title and price dynamically.
70. **Canonical URLs:** Ensure every page defines a `<link rel="canonical">` to prevent duplicate content penalties from faceted navigation or tracking tags.
71. **404 Tracking:** Catch 404 visits in Google Analytics to see which broken links users are hitting most often, and set up 301 redirects.
72. **SEO-Friendly URLs:** Ensure product URLs use slugs (`/product/black-hoodie-01`) instead of raw IDs (`/product/1a2b3c...`).
73. **Social Proof Widgets:** Add a small text ticker on the product page: "2 people bought this in the last 24 hours" (can be mocked safely or tied to simplified metrics).
74. **Share Buttons:** Add simple native Web Share API buttons on mobile (`navigator.share()`) for easy sending via iMessage/WhatsApp.
75. **Newsletter Intent:** Rather than a popup, integrate the newsletter signup naturally at the bottom of high-traffic articles or Tour pages.
76. **Mobile Tap Target Areas:** Continually audit buttons to ensure they are at least `min-h-[44px]` and `min-w-[44px]` for fat-finger clicking.
77. **Text Resizing Support:** Ensure UI doesn't completely break if a user has their device font set to 150% in OS accessibility settings.
78. **H1 Hierarchy:** Ensure absolutely every page has exactly one `<h1>` tag, and it contains the most important keyword for that page.
79. **Reduced Motion Adherence:** Respect the OS `prefers-reduced-motion` flag and disable heavy Framer Motion animations for users who request it.
80. **Brand Keyword Optimization:** Audit the homepage copy to ensure exact target keywords ("South African luxury streetwear", "brutalist clothing") are naturally present.

